    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "##Investigate and Modify\r\n\r\nExperiment with the program by making the following modifications, then run the program to observe the results.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO:** Take a look at the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getRecommendedMeatRecipes()</code> method in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">RecipeBlog</code> class. Should this method be <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">public</code> or <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">private</code>?\r\n\r\nReplace the code you added to the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">RecipeRunner</code> class with the following code segment :\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #333333; color: white;\">\r\nSystem.out.println(\"Recommended meat recipes: \" + blog.getRecommendedMeatRecipes());\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nTry changing the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">recipesToString()</code> method back to <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">private</code>, then run the program. Does this change the functionality of the program? Why or why not?",
    "mini_rubric": "false",
    "submittable": "false",
    "hide_share_and_remix": "false",
    "csa_view_mode": "console",
    "start_sources": {
      "Runner.java": {
        "text": "public class Runner {\n  public static void main(String[] args) {\n\n    /* ----------------------------------- TO DO -----------------------------------\n     * ✅ instructions for the student to complete\n     * -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n     */\n\n\n\n    /* ----------------------------------- TO DO -----------------------------------\n     * ✅ instructions for the student to complete\n     * -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n     *\n     * description of method to write\n     */\n\n    \n\n    \n    /* ---- 🔎 ADD YOUR CODE BELOW THIS LINE ---- */\n\n\n    \n    \n    \n  }\n}",
        "isVisible": true,
